snippet.textDisplay:
This honestly seems a bit skewed in Ashens' favour with how it is set up. I don't know how much the baby calendar cost, but the Fortnite calendar has the apparent advantage of a higher price allowing for higher value individual items.

Perhaps next year (Dan's life enduring) they could have a way to account for calendar prices, such as:
•Dividing the calendar price by 25 and judging each item in direct relation to that price value.
•Giving items a score out of 10 and giving extra points to the rating according to the price difference between calendars.

...I'm already putting way too much thought into this.
